Package: spBPS
Title: Univariate and Multivariate Accelerated Spatial Modeling by Bayesian Predictive Stacking
Version: 0.0-1
Authors@R: 
    c(person("Luca", "Presicce", , "l.presicce@campus.unimib.it", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0005-7062-3523")), 
     person("Sudipto", "Banerjee", role="aut", email="sudipto@ucla.edu"))
Maintainer: Luca Presicce <l.presicce@campus.unimib.it>
Author: Luca Presicce [aut, cre], Sudipto Banerjee [aut]
Description: This package provides the computational framework to fit the accelerated spatial regression models following the approach presented and detailed in "Bayesian Transfer Learning for Artificially Intelligent Geospatial Systems: A Predictive Stacking Approach" of Presicce L., and Banerjee S. (2024) <doi:10.48550/arXiv.2410.09504>. The functions in the package use mostly Rcpp-armadillo implementations, offering computationally efficient Bayesian geostatistical modeling, ready for high performance computing and parallel environments.
Depends: R (>= 1.8.0)
Imports: Rcpp, CVXR
LinkingTo: mniw, mvnfast, Rcpp, RcppArmadillo
Suggests: testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
License: GPL (>= 3)
Encoding: UTF-8
